      "side": 1,
      "message": "+1\n\nIf the task cares what version of Windows it runs on, the task name should include the version. I suspect that\u0027s true for Perf and Test tasks.\n\nIf the task doesn\u0027t care, we shouldn\u0027t include the version in the dimensions.\n\nIMO, same goes for Mac, Ubuntu, etc., at least where we don\u0027t map from device type to OS version. But I don\u0027t think it matters enough to do a mass rename for those.",
      "parentUuid": "f01d104e_4c621ac1",
      "revId": "4bd289888430bd29f571c995d8638ea8fdb149ea",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f01d104e_02be2998",
        "filename": "infra/bots/gen_tasks.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 148,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-11-30T20:21:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Okay, changed the Test and Perf Win- bots to Win2k8.\n\nI disagree about the task not caring.  The task may not care what version of the OS it runs on, but we probably do care that it doesn\u0027t change without notice.  IMO specifying a version in dimensions is helpful since it allows us to upgrade in lockstep with a commit.\n\nWe need to decide soon what the policy will be for supporting different OS versions.  If we actually want to test multiple versions, then we should include the versions in the builder names when we care.  Otherwise, we should just choose a single version of each OS and not include it in the builder name.  Either way, I think we should specify the version as a dimension.",
      "parentUuid": "2d82efcd_39924b37",
      "revId": "4bd289888430bd29f571c995d8638ea8fdb149ea",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f01d104e_0249c9d1",
        "filename": "infra/bots/gen_tasks.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 148,
      "author": {
        "id": 5010
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-11-30T20:37:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Eric\u0027s plan here sounds good to me.\n\nGenerally, the Test bots may care about OS version they run on, but mostly only for things like fonts that vary from release to release, annoyingly both major and minor.\n\nGenerally, the Perf bots don\u0027t care about what OS version they run on, and it\u0027s nice to be stable.\n\nAll the GPU bots probably do care about driver versions, which is sometimes coupled to the OS (Android, Mac) and sometimes not (Win, Linux).\n\nSo, now while some bots may care about the OS they use, I don\u0027t know that each of those bots has a human that particularly cares it exists, especially w.r.t Win 8 or 10.  I certainly don\u0027t.  I\u0027d be happy with everything on the latest everything.  You probably want to consult with bungeman to see about fonts, and if he doesn\u0027t care, we can update all bots to consistent OS versions (and re-drop the version suffixes).",
      "parentUuid": "f01d104e_02be2998",
      "revId": "4bd289888430bd29f571c995d8638ea8fdb149ea",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
